author: Alexander Betser
comment: Pros: - Two dimensional data model (projects and plural tags). - Activity timer. - Moderately clean and streamlined user interface. - Advanced backup/restore to SD card, Dropbox, Google Drive in easy to read XML format. - Usable CSV export format for external analysis. - Tag-time and project-time reports. - Geofence and WIFI -triggered start/stop/toggle of project task. - Hourly billing rate.  Cons: - Limited filtering of tasks (billing status only). - Inability to navigate from pie chart to actual tasks that make up slices. - Lack of tag and project timeline report (how metric changes over time).

author: josh cagle
comment: Great app for keeping up with hours on different projects. Very flexible. One bit of feedback though.  If I forget to clock in and go back and edit the time, the automatic break after "x" hours is based on the original time I clocked in not the edited time.  This is a minor annoyance and I would still recommend this app to all

author: christine Francis
comment: This has been the best time tracking app I've used. I was constantly forgetting to log hours worked on projects and probably cost myself several thousand dollars in unreported man hours. This one is convenient and easy to use.

author: Anita Woodruff
comment: This app has just got better and better. I love the stats view with the donut rings in different colours. I use it to track what I'm doing at work for my own productivity/interest and it works really well for that.

author: Bryan Tribolet
comment: Two things would make this app perfect for small business. 1. Ability to export archived projects. 2. Project "revenue rate", as opposed to salary, a revenue rate would allow you to distinguish from business income, which is marginally higher than personal income. Otherwise, great app!

author: Matthew Redmond-Lyon
comment: Great timesheet app has loads of features like stats, different projects and rates and the smiley face rate my task feature is nice at the end of the day. One great improvement would be to select a default rate while on a project because I'm on a particular rate for multiple weeks in a row maybe indefinitely so would like my phone to know that.

author: William Marchetti
comment: This is a very well laid out app and is extremely  intuitive and easy to use.  The Developer has been resposive to questions.  I have just enrolled in the annual plus plan as it serves as an excellent timekeeping tool both in the field  and in the office.

author: James Smith
comment: I work as a contractor and need to split my time between 5 different charge numbers. I also have the expectation to log a certain amount of hours in a two week period. This app helps me get organized with all of that.
